header.gameNote: FLINT HILLS RESOURCES ISLANDER CLASSIC AT CORPUS CHRISTI TX

article.headline: James Madison 79, Yale 69
article.story: CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas (AP) -- Jomo Belfor scored 28 points, including 15 on free throws, and James Madison hit 12 3-pointers in a 79-69 victory against Yale in the first round of the Islanders Classic on Thursday night. James Madison (3-5) will play the Savannah State-Texas A&M-Corpus Christi winner in the tournament championship Friday. Belfor was 5-of-11 from the field, including 3-of-5 on 3-pointers, and made 15 of 16 free throws. He led the Dukes with seven rebounds. Ray Barbosa had 17 points and was 4-of-8 from 3-point range. James Madison made 12 of 23 from long range. Sam Kaplan scored 16 points, and Nick Holmes had 12 points and 11 rebounds to lead Yale (5-6). James Madison shot 55 percent while building a 44-29 halftime lead.
